                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 836/123.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to bring to
                    your knowledge that, according to a communication just received from the
                    Brazilian Government, by a decree No. 7283, of the 14th of January instant, the
                    ministry of finance renewed for the present fiscal year the reduction of 20 per
                    cent previously granted to the American flour and to other articles imported in
                    Brazil from the United States of America.</p>
                <p>I avail, etc,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joaquim Nabuco.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
